<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1744,2023]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1744,1770]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ranjan &amp; Singh &amp; Kirti, 2022" authorityName="Ranjan &amp; Singh &amp; Kirti" authorityYear="2022" box="[285,447,1745,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mizo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[285,447,1745,1770]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Locastra mizo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[456,548,1745,1771]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[456,548,1745,1771]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[566,635,1744,1771]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1716,1740]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,468,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,453,1692]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Adults. Locastra spp.: 1, L. muscosalis, male; 2, L. viridis, male; 3, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 4, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911335/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[824,979,1744,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muscosalis">
<emphasis box="[824,979,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. muscosalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group and is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[240,309,1780,1807]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1716,1740]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,468,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,453,1692]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Adults. Locastra spp.: 1, L. muscosalis, male; 2, L. viridis, male; 3, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 4, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911335/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), but is distinct by the medial area of the forewing being less suffused with reddish brown (medial area conspicuously reddish brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[578,682,1816,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[578,682,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the antemedial line almost straight (antemedial line zigzag in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the fulvous markings at the centre of the forewing costa outlined with fuscous (fuscous patch absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,253,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[151,253,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ranjan &amp; Singh &amp; Kirti, 2022" authorityName="Ranjan &amp; Singh &amp; Kirti" authorityYear="2022" box="[520,602,1889,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mizo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[520,602,1889,1914]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. mizo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[609,701,1889,1915]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[609,694,1889,1915]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[716,783,1888,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,197,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[155,1432,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. Locastra spp.: 7, L. muscosalis, male; 8, L. viridis, male; 9, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 10, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911343/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) is distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[976,1077,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[976,1077,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1092,1159,1888,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,197,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[155,1432,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. Locastra spp.: 7, L. muscosalis, male; 8, L. viridis, male; 9, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 10, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911343/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) by the longer vinculum and juxta, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[402,505,1924,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[402,505,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the vinculum is only about twice as long as the tegumen, and the juxta is shorter. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ranjan &amp; Singh &amp; Kirti, 2022" authorityName="Ranjan &amp; Singh &amp; Kirti" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,311,1961,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mizo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,311,1961,1986]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Locastra mizo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[317,407,1961,1987]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[317,407,1961,1987]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is also distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[642,766,1960,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solivaga">
<emphasis box="[642,766,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. solivaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rong, H. &amp; Li, H." box="[781,970,1960,1987]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" pagination="101 - 118" refId="ref4223" refString="Rong, H. &amp; Li, H. (2017) Review of the genus Locastra Walker, 1859 from China, with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera, Pyralidae, Epipaschiinae). ZooKeys, 724, 101 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 724.13262" type="journal article" year="2017">Rong &amp; Li 2017</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 12) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1117,1270,1960,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muscosalis">
<emphasis box="[1117,1270,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. muscosalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1285,1352,1960,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,197,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[155,1432,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. Locastra spp.: 7, L. muscosalis, male; 8, L. viridis, male; 9, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 10, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911343/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) by the vinculum being almost three times longer than the tegumen, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[943,1069,1996,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solivaga">
<emphasis box="[943,1069,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. solivaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1126,1280,1996,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muscosalis">
<emphasis box="[1126,1280,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. muscosalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the vinculum and tegumen are almost equally long. Furthermore, the new species is distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[1074,1233,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtrapezia">
<emphasis box="[1074,1233,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">L. subtrapezia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rong, H. &amp; Li, H." box="[1246,1432,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" pagination="101 - 118" refId="ref4223" refString="Rong, H. &amp; Li, H. (2017) Review of the genus Locastra Walker, 1859 from China, with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera, Pyralidae, Epipaschiinae). ZooKeys, 724, 101 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 724.13262" type="journal article" year="2017">Rong &amp; Li 2017</bibRefCitation>
: figs 5, 10) by the basal area of the forewing being black, and the uncus with a broad apex, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[1277,1437,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtrapezia">
<emphasis box="[1277,1437,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">L. subtrapezia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basal area of the forewing is pale olivaceous fuscous, and the uncus is rectangular. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Joannis 1930: 631)" baseAuthorityName="Joannis" baseAuthorityPageNumber="631" baseAuthorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bryalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">L. bryalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Joannis, J. de" box="[243,448,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" pagination="559 - 834" refId="ref3869" refString="Joannis, J. de. (1930) Lepidopteres Heteroceres du Tonkin. 3 e partie. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, Paris, 98 (1929), 559 - 834." type="journal article" year="1930">Joannis 1930: 631</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the hindwing being uniformly fuscous and the postmedial line being absent, whereas in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Joannis" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[180,289,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bryalis">
<emphasis box="[180,289,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">L. bryalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basal area of the hindwing is whitish, and the postmedial line is well marked, outwardly bordered with whitish, and inwardly bordered with blackish.
</paragraph>
